snippet.textDisplay:
Googoosh is Iran's Iconic singer. Anyone who grew up listening to persian music knows this song and the singer. Yet here we are producing a below average version of the song. Gul Panra, was a misfit from the moment she opened her mouth. I initially tolerated Gul because of Atif but he some how managed it to drop to new lows with his typical pop composition, which was off pitch in some places and ending with complete disaster.

Rohail Hayatt also used the music of this iconic song as instrumental piece in one of the CS song... I consider that a much better trubute than this version.

Sorry Googoosh on behalf of all pakistani music lovers.

I like this. I'm American, and I am amazed by the number of hateful comments here -- all coming from Middle Eastern people. Hate as well as tolerance are certainly universal. : / 

At first I was going to say that this is 'Indian Progressive Rock', but I see several clarifications that this was on Pakistani television. I dig it, and the studio envvironment. I'm glad that Coke has such a big presence which allows support of a project like this. I was trying to identify the brand of drums the trap set player is using. Neat stuff. ; ]
